FT  03 JUN 93 / Absenteeism costs Ireland dear
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM COONE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Absenteeism, mostly due to certified illness, is costing Irish business an
estimated IPounds 600m (Pounds 580m) a year, with some 12m working days
being lost in 1992, according to a report by the Irish Business and
Employers' Federation, writes Tim Coone in Dublin. That was 65 times higher
than losses through strikes.
The report said 4.5 per cent of available working time was being lost in
this way. This compares with 3.5 per cent in the UK.
