FT  02 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Blacks agrees sale of LA Gear business
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Blacks Leisure Group has agreed the sale of its LA Gear distribution
business, including certain fixed assets and stocks, to LA Gear Inc for
Pounds 1.65m.
Of the purchase price Pounds 1.4m will be paid on completion. The
consideration will be subject to adjustment following a post completion
stocktake.
In addition, the distribution agreement between LA Gear and Blacks'
wholly-owned subsidiary, All American Footwear Corporation, will be
cancelled in exchange for a payment of Pounds 700,000.
