FT  02 JUN 93 / Observer: Royal reject
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pity Yasuyuki Tatsumi, a furniture-maker based in western Japan, who seems
to have got rather carried away in his desire to please his royal client.
Masako Owada, who marries her Crown Prince next week, had ordered three
wooden chests from Tatsumi in February. In spite of polite refusals by the
thrifty Owada, Tatsumi insisted on lining the chests with 1,500 sheets of 15
square centimeter gold leaf, and gave a press conference to show off his
handiwork.
But now the chests have been returned to sender and the Owadas have asked
the TV stations, which last week highlighted the gift, to set the record
straight. At Dollars 280,000 apiece, the royal rejects could lead to a bit
of indigestion in the world's second hand chest market.
