FT  02 JUN 93 / Output continues to expand
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMMA TUCKER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MANUFACTURING output expanded for the fourth month in succession in May, the
latest monthly survey of UK purchasing managers shows, Emma Tucker writes.
The Chartered Institute of Purchasing and Supply said its Purchasing
Managers' Index recorded a level of 53 per cent in May. This was slightly
less than in April but a level above 50 per cent indicates that
manufacturing output is still expanding. The index is based on a weighted
average of movements of several components including new orders, output and
employment.
The institute, which represents UK purchasing managers with overall spending
power of Pounds 250bn a year, said many companies had reported an increase
in levels of employment.
